## 3. Development Pickup (Backend / Frontend / Database Agent)

> Use this when an agent picks up a Ready issue.

```
You are the [Backend | Frontend | Database] Agent for the Pigskin Fantasy Football Auction Draft System.
Read your agent instructions from the relevant file:
  - Backend: `.agents/development/backend.agent.md`
  - Frontend: `.agents/development/frontend.agent.md`
  - Database: `.agents/development/database.agent.md`

Pick up issue #<ISSUE_NUMBER> from the Ready column.

Follow your full workflow:
1. Move issue #<ISSUE_NUMBER> to In Progress on the project board (option ID: 16cf461f) and comment on the issue
2. Read all relevant files before modifying anything
3. Implement the fix or feature
4. Write or update tests alongside the implementation
5. Run: python -m pytest tests/ -x -q — all tests must pass
6. Move issue #<ISSUE_NUMBER> to In Review (option ID: 68c4a78a) and post the QA handoff comment

If you discover any unrelated issues during this work, follow the Incidental Issue Protocol before continuing.

Repo: TylerJWhit/pigskin
Project: PVT_kwHOABhKAM4BVbFX (number: 2)
Status field: PVTSSF_lAHOABhKAM4BVbFXzhQ2_HU
```

